Description: Sixty-nine stone fragments set in two slabs of modern plaster. There are 25 pieces in the smaller slab and the remaining 44 are in the larger one. The fragments vary in size from substantial pieces with clear remains of relief decoration or hieroglyphs to tiny fragments bearing little more than incised lines.Subjects include such elements as a royal face, the Red Crown, parts of a pair of cartouches (probably of Nekhthorheb) and part of a star-frieze.
Curator's comments: See Brissaud and Zivie-Coche - Tanis 1987-1997 (Paris, 1998) p.107 [33].
Setting the fragments in plaster and sending them to the British Museum is mentioned in Petrie, Tanis, I, 28.
